that idea , too , fell through , and the property was finally sold at bid .
it was purchased by anchorage attorney bill ingaldson .
he was not returning calls on tuesday .
ingaldson , as well as the state division of agriculture and other property owners , have been in negotiations with the city of palmer on the sale of what is called the old "matanuska maid block . " .
it is an area of about 8 . 7 acres near downtown palmer that included , until tuesday , the old creamery , an historic hatchery , a cinderblock power house , a residency , a building housing the offices of the palmer arts council , and crowley petroleum distributors , which maintains the fuel storage facility .
palmer voters in 2010 approved a $3 million bond to pay for purchase of the property .
