mat maid the state - owned corporation was a company that struggled from the start and sold a lot of milk produced in the lower 48 .
"in 2004 , 39 percent of the milk produced at mat maid was from alaska producers , " the white paper said .
the other 61 percent was shipped in from outside to be packaged and sold as alaska milk in an effort by mat maid to maintain market share in hopes the cows on the state - sponsored farms at point mackenzie would one day start producing .
